headline: Marriott International Named One of the Top 2025 World's Best Workplaces by Fortune and Great Place To Work
summary: Today, Marriott International, Inc. announced it has been named one of the top five World's Best Workplaces by Great Place To Work® and Fortune magazine.

headline: HWE confirms sale of 131-room Residence Inn hotel in Baltimore
summary: A team from HWE, led by managing director Clint Hodges and senior vice-president Nate Ries, acted on behalf of the seller.

headline: What’s next for Marriott after Sonder collapse?
summary: Marriott is still excited about brand growth in the apartment-style space after terminating its long-term licensing agreement with beleaguered Sonder.
